						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Ah. It combines /CE with the battery IC's +CE to allow a 32768x8 SRAM to be protected, whereas normally they'd have to use some SRAM with two enables.</div><br />Yeah, the register $A130F1 (what you'd officially write to if you had a full blown mapper) has this format: ??????WE, where W = allow writing and E = enable SRAM (it needs to be 00 to make SRAM hidden and 11 to make SRAM writeable).</div>

